  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GardenAfrica - Organisational Development Grant</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GardenAfrica (GA) works with partners to improve awareness of natural resource management issues, providing training to improve education, health and livelihoods through the establishment of safe and sustainable environments. GA&#x2019;s partnerships have facilitated the sharing of expertise and skills to increase local capacity, and build a wider network to foster trans-disciplinary approaches where such opportunities may not previously have existed.  However, GA has limited capacity and no adequate structure to capture and apply lessons learnt and to use this learning to advocate for change. 
In order to do this and better support and strengthen their partners GA need appropriate tools. Furthermore, if GA is to grow strategically with a view to continued innovation, it must consider how best to capture and collate learning, and disseminate findings in order to increase the impact of its work. They have already refreshed their board of trustees and this OD planning grant would enable them to finalise their next five-year strategy and use external expertise to develop a more appropriate M&amp;E framework and advocacy plan.</narrative>
  </description>
